Just to let you know -- I can&#39;t use JUnitX because it is too reliant on
Java2. On Windows, I&#39;m using IBM JRE, which is not Java2.

On the Macintosh, you should know that MacOS 7/8/9 will _never_ support
Java2. This is mostly for technical reasons [Apple having difficulty in
porting Sun&#39;s sources], but it also serves to motivate people to upgrade to
MacOS X, which will not be shipping in a final form until next year.

